ary plant ecology: assumptions, parameters and prescriptions (1999) Bot. Rev., 65, pp. 39-75; Jermstad, K., Bassoni, D.L., Jech, K.S., Wheeler, N.C., Neale, D.B., Mapping of quantitative trait loci controlling adaptive traits in coastal Douglas-fir. I. Timing of vegetative bud flush (2001) Theor. Appl. Gen., 102, pp. 1142-1151; Kellomäki, S., Peltola, H., Nuutinen, T., Korhonen, K.T., Strandman, H., Sensitivity of managed boreal forests in Finland to climate change, with implications for adaptive management (2008) Phil. Trans. R. Soc. B, 363, pp. 2341-2351; Kramer, K., Buiteveld, J., Forstreuter, M., Geburek, T., Leonardi, S., Menozzi, P., Povillon, F., van der Werf, D.C., Bridging the gap between ecophysiological and genetic knowledge to assess the adaptive potential of European beech (2008) Ecol. Model., 216, pp. 333-353; Kuparinen, A., Markkanen, T., Riikonen, H., Vesala, T., Modeling air-mediated dispersal of spores, pollen and seeds in forested areas (2007) Ecol. Model., 208, pp. 177-188; Kuparinen, A., Schurr, F.M., A flexible modeling framework linking spatio-temporal dynamics of plant genotypes and populations: application to gene flow from transgenic forests (2007) Ecol. Model., 202, pp. 476-486; Kuparinen, A., Katul, G., Nathan, R., Schurr, F.M., Increases in air temperature can promote wind-driven dispersal and spread of plants (2009) Proc. R. Soc. B, 276, pp. 3081-3087; Luquez, V., Hall, D., Albrectsen, B.R., Karlsson, J., Ingvarsson, P., Jansson, S., Natural phenological variation in aspen (Populus tremula): the SwAsp collection (2008) Tree Genet. Genomes, 4, pp. 279-292; Marris, E., Planting the forest of the future (2009) Nature, 459, pp. 906-908; Meehl, G.A., Stocker, T.F., Collins, W.D., Friedlingstein, P., Gayen, A.T., Gregory, J.M., Kitoh, A., Knutti, R., Murphy, J.M., Noda, A., Raper, S.C.B., Watterson, I.G., Weaver, A.J., Zhao Z.-C., 2007. Global climate projections. In: Solomon, S., Qin, D., Manning, M., Chen, Z., Marquis, M., Averyt, K.B., Tig